# CabinetPlus Electron Migration Tasks

## 0) Decisions and baseline
- [ ] Confirm runtime approach: run Next.js as an embedded local server in Electron (recommended for App Router + server actions).
- [ ] Freeze current web behavior as baseline (login flow, dashboard navigation, pages load without errors).
- [ ] Define desktop targets: Windows first, then macOS/Linux.
- [ ] Add migration branch strategy and milestone tags (M1 shell, M2 data, M3 packaging).

## 1) Project structure changes
- [ ] Create `electron/` folder with:
  - [ ] `electron/main.ts` (app lifecycle + BrowserWindow)
  - [ ] `electron/preload.ts` (safe bridge for IPC)
  - [ ] `electron/ipc/` (handlers grouped by domain)
  - [ ] `electron/security.ts` (window/webPreferences hardening)
  - [ ] `electron/paths.ts` (userData/db/log paths)
- [ ] Keep Next app in `app/` as renderer UI (no rewrite to pure React renderer).
- [ ] Add `shared/` for cross-process types (DTOs, request/response contracts, event names).

## 2) Tooling and scripts
- [ ] Add Electron runtime/build deps (`electron`, `electron-builder` or `electron-forge`, `concurrently`, `wait-on`, `cross-env`).
- [ ] Add TypeScript config for Electron process (`tsconfig.electron.json`).
- [ ] Add scripts to `package.json`:
  - [ ] `dev:next` -> `next dev`
  - [ ] `dev:electron` -> run Electron after Next port is ready
  - [ ] `dev:desktop` -> run both processes together
  - [ ] `build:web` -> `next build`
  - [ ] `build:electron` -> compile/package Electron
  - [ ] `build:desktop` -> full distributable build
- [ ] Ensure lint covers Electron and shared folders.

## 3) Electron main process foundation
- [ ] Create BrowserWindow with strict defaults:
  - [ ] `contextIsolation: true`
  - [ ] `nodeIntegration: false`
  - [ ] `sandbox: true` (if compatible)
  - [ ] preload script enabled
- [ ] Dev mode: load `http://localhost:<port>` from Next dev server.
- [ ] Prod mode: start Next server programmatically and load local URL.
- [ ] Add single-instance lock and clean app shutdown handling.
- [ ] Add centralized error logging for main process startup and IPC failures.

## 4) Preload and IPC contract
- [ ] Define namespaced API exposed to renderer, example:
  - [ ] `window.cabinet.auth.*`
  - [ ] `window.cabinet.patients.*`
  - [ ] `window.cabinet.consultations.*`
  - [ ] `window.cabinet.revenue.*`
- [ ] Build typed IPC request/response contracts in `shared/`.
- [ ] Implement input validation for every IPC handler (zod recommended).
- [ ] Add uniform error shape for renderer consumption (`code`, `message`, `details`).
- [ ] Add IPC timeout and cancellation strategy for long operations.

## 5) Database setup (replace mock constants)
- [ ] Choose DB: SQLite recommended for desktop offline-first.
- [ ] Choose ORM/query layer (`Prisma` or `Drizzle`), then standardize on one.
- [ ] Create schema for core entities:
  - [ ] `users`
  - [ ] `patients`
  - [ ] `appointments`
  - [ ] `consultations`
  - [ ] `consultation_treatments`
  - [ ] `revenues` (or derive from billing records)
- [ ] Add migration system and initial migration.
- [ ] Store DB file in Electron `app.getPath("userData")`, not project root.
- [ ] Add seed script to populate development data equivalent to `app/constants.ts`.
- [ ] Add backup/restore strategy (manual export first, automation later).

## 6) Repository layer
- [ ] Add repositories per aggregate (pure data access, no UI logic):
  - [ ] `PatientRepository`
  - [ ] `AppointmentRepository`
  - [ ] `ConsultationRepository`
  - [ ] `RevenueRepository`
  - [ ] `UserRepository`
- [ ] Standardize repository return types (success/result patterns).
- [ ] Add pagination/filter/sort contracts for list queries.
- [ ] Add transaction support for multi-write flows.
- [ ] Add repository unit tests against a temp SQLite DB.

## 7) Handler/service layer
- [ ] Build service layer between IPC and repositories:
  - [ ] `AuthService`
  - [ ] `PatientService`
  - [ ] `ConsultationService`
  - [ ] `SchedulingService`
  - [ ] `RevenueService`
- [ ] Implement business rules currently implicit in UI (validation, defaults, statuses).
- [ ] Move login behavior from cookie-only mock to persisted user/session model.
- [ ] Keep server actions only where needed; prefer IPC for desktop-only operations.
- [ ] Add audit events for create/update/delete actions.

## 8) Frontend integration tasks
- [ ] Replace direct `MOCK_*` usage with data hooks/services that call `window.cabinet` API.
- [ ] Add query/state library (TanStack Query recommended) for caching and invalidation.
- [ ] Create feature data modules by route group:
  - [ ] `app/(dashboard)/patients` data bindings
  - [ ] `app/(dashboard)/consultations` data bindings
  - [ ] `app/(dashboard)/calendar` data bindings
  - [ ] `app/(dashboard)/revenue` data bindings
- [ ] Add optimistic updates only where rollback is defined.
- [ ] Add loading, empty, and error states on all data screens.
- [ ] Keep using `app/components/ui/primitives.tsx` for consistent controls.

## 9) Auth/session redesign for desktop
- [ ] Replace middleware cookie gate with desktop session state source.
- [ ] Keep route guard behavior equivalent to current `middleware.ts` paths.
- [ ] Add secure credential storage plan:
  - [ ] local hashed credentials for offline mode, or
  - [ ] token storage via OS keychain (`keytar`) if remote auth is added.
- [ ] Add logout that clears in-memory and persisted session artifacts.

## 10) Security hardening
- [ ] Disable remote module and unneeded web APIs.
- [ ] Define strict Content Security Policy for renderer.
- [ ] Validate and sanitize all IPC payloads.
- [ ] Prevent arbitrary file path access in handlers.
- [ ] Add dependency audit check in CI/pre-release.

